planGroups.title: Accounting - Critical Tracking Progress
planGroups.description:
To graduate with this major, students must complete all university, college and major requirements.

Equivalent critical tracking courses as determined by the State of Florida Common Course Prerequisites may be used for transfer students.

Additional information regarding general education
   *  Students are required to complete two composition courses for a total of 3 hours.
   *  Students are required to complete two math courses for a total of 6 hours.
   *  Students may vary the hours in humanities, social and behavioral sciences, and physical and 
   biological sciences to have no fewer than six hours and no more than 12 hours in each category
   with a total of 24 hours among the three categories.
    * General education requirements may be fulfilled with credit from AP, IB or dual-enrollment 
   courses. Additional exemptions may occur from SAT II scores, if deemed appropriate. The 
   3000/4000-level business core courses will not satisfy general education requirements (for 
   example, MAN 3025 and MAR 3023).

Semester 1

    * Complete 2 of the 8 critical-tracking courses: ACG 2021, ACG 2071, CGS 2531, ECO 2013, ECO
   2023, MAC 2233, MAC 2234, STA 2023
    * 3.0 GPA required on all attempts of preprofessional courses
    * 3.0 UF GPA required

Semester 2

    * Complete 2 additional courses of the 8 critical-tracking courses (1 of the 4 courses must be MAC 
   2233 or equivalent)
    * 3.0 GPA required on all attempts of preprofessional courses
    * 3.0 UF GPA required

Semester 3

    * Complete 2 additional courses of the 8 critical-tracking courses (1 of the 6 courses must be ACG
   2021 with a minimum grade of B)
    * 3.0 GPA required on all attempts of preprofessional courses
    * 3.0 UF GPA required

Semester 4

    * Complete all 8 critical-tracking courses (ACG 2071 must be completed with a minimum grade of
   B)
    * Complete general education and the university writing and math requirements.
    * 3.0 GPA required on all attempts of preprofessional courses
    * 3.0 UF GPA required

Semester 5

    * Complete ACG 3101 or ACG 3401
    * Complete 2 of the 7 business core courses: BUL 4310, FIN 3403, GEB 3373, MAN 3025, MAN 4504, MAR 3023, QMB 3250
    * 3.0 GPA required on all attempts of preprofessional courses
    * 3.0 UF GPA required

Semester 6

    * Complete ACG 3101 and ACG 3401 with a C or better
    * Complete 4 of the 7 business core courses, including FIN 3403 and QMB 3250
    * 2.0 GPA required on all accounting courses number 3000 and above
    * 2.0 upper-division GPA required (all courses taken after the student earned 60 credits)
    * 2.0 UF GPA required

Semester 7

    * Complete ACG 4111 and ACG 4341 with a C or better
    * Complete 6 of the 7 business core courses
    * 2.0 GPA required on all accounting courses number 3000 and above
    * 2.0 upper-division GPA required (all courses taken after the student earned 60 credits)
    * 2.0 UF GPA required

Semester 8

    * Complete ACG 4632 (or ACG 5637 and ACG 5647)
    * Complete TAX 4001 (or TAX 5025 and TAX 5027)
    * Complete all 7 business core courses
    * Complete all other degree requirements
    * 2.0 GPA required on all accounting courses number 3000 and above
    * 2.0 upper-division GPA required (all courses taken after the student earned 60 credits)
    * 2.0 UF GPA required

planGroups.title: Accounting - Common Prerequisites for Transfer Admission

requirements.title: Major Specific State Common Prerequisites
requirements.description:
The following are prerequisites for upper division transfer into the program for students with an articulated Associate of Arts degree.

Minimum Admission Standards for Students with state-articulated AA Degree

*** This is a limited access program ***

1. Minimum 3.0 GPA on all attempts of required courses
2. Required overall GPA of 3.0
3. Minimum grade of B or better required for ACG2021 within two attempts (including withdrawals and drops)
4. Complete AA degree and general education courses
5. Complete University Writing Requirement
6. Complete two sequential courses of the same foreign language in high school or 8-10 credits at post-secondary level, or document an equivalent level of proficiency.
